X_1,X_2,\ldots,
(0,1)
N=\min\{n>0\mid X_{(n)}-X_{(1)}>\alpha\}
0<\alpha<1
\mathbb{E}(N)
X_{(1)},X_{(n)}
X_1,X_2,\ldots,
\alpha
    \mathbb{P}(N_\alpha = n) = (n-1) \left(1-\alpha\right)^2 \alpha^{n-2} 
   \mathbb{E}(N_\alpha) = \sum_{n=1}^\infty n \cdot (n-1) \left(1-\alpha\right)^2 \alpha^{n-2}  =  \left(1-\alpha\right)^2  \frac{\mathrm{d}^2}{\mathrm{d} \alpha^2} \frac{1}{1-\alpha} = \frac{2}{1-\alpha} 
